        <p><strong>Tom Poppendieck</strong> has over 25 years of experience in computing including eight years of work with object technology.</p>
        <p>His modelling and mentoring skills are rooted in his experience as a physics professor.</p>
        <p>His early work was in IT infrastructure, product development, and manufacturing support, and evolved to consulting project assignments in healthcare, logistics, mortgage banking, and travel services.</p>
        <p>Tom led the development of a world class product data management practice for a major commercial avionics manufacturer that reduced design to production transition efforts from 6 months to 6 weeks.</p>
        <p>Tom Poppendieck is an enterprise analyst and architect, and an <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('agile', 'PM'); ?> process mentor.</p>
        <p>He focuses on identifying real business value and enabling product teams to realize that value.</p>
        <p>Tom specializes in understanding customer processes and in effective collaboration of customer, development and support specialists to maximize development efficiency, system flexibility, and business value.</p>
        <p>Tom is co-author of the book <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Lean Software Development: An Agile Toolkit', 'B'); ?>, published in 2003, its sequel, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Implementing Lean Software Development: From Concept to Cash', 'B'); ?>, published in 2006, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Leading Lean Software Development: Results are Not the Point', 'B'); ?> in 2009, and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('The Lean Mindset: Ask the Right Questions', 'B'); ?> in 2013.</p>
